{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For instance, (Okura et al. 2017) proposed to learn news embeddings from article bodies using denoising autoencoders and capture user interests using GRU networks.",
    "(Wang et al. 2018) introduced a knowledgeaware CNN that incorporates information from knowledge graphs to encode news titles.",
    "These approaches often rely on a single type of news information (e.g., title or body), which may be insufficient for learning comprehensive news and user representations.",
    "Our approach, in contrast, employs the multi-view news encoder of NAML to integrate diverse information sources such as titles, abstracts, and categories, providing a richer and more accurate representation of news content.",
    "Attention mechanisms have been widely applied in neural news recommendation, including personalized attention networks (Wu et al. 2019b) and multi-head self-attention (Wu et al. 2019c), to highlight informative words or articles."
  ],
